In article <Feb.24.11.45.02.1994.10236@remus.rutgers.edu> wclark@remus.rutgers.edu (Bill Clark) writes:
>			If you want something more secure than RSA, just
>modify the algorithm to use more than two factors


This is bad advice.  The difficulty of factoring has to do with the size of
the second largest factor, not with the number of factors.


